Subject: Dictated Periphery Correlation Potential Scan Source

Description: Preserved source note for scanning whether the periphery of recent developments correlates with other already-developed periphery to reveal new potential utility.

& [DictatedPeripheryCorrelationPotentialScanSource] is the preserved user request
  + [source_status] is preserved_raw_direction
  + [captured_request] is does the periphery of these developments correlate to other periphery of other work already developed, to reveal new potentials and desirable utility
  + [active_development_context] is Social Periphery Interest Fabric, SOP Swarm Fabric, Local AI Manager Primary, periphery overlap, trust-lensed recommendations, and local manager routing
  + [requested_operation] is scan nearby existing SOP periphery for correlation, utility, and desirable future direction
  + [preservation_boundary] is source direction only, not canonical specification authority until separately processed
  + [outside] is implementation, crawler automation, social graph capture, remote sharing, proof of truth, and hidden model-state claims

  = must: preserve the question shape before canonicalizing the scan
  = must: keep correlation as possibility and route evidence through existing SOP files
  = must: preserve implementation outside until gates are named
